---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PrimaryCTA from '../../components/PrimaryCTA.astro';
import AuthorBio from '../../components/AuthorBio.astro';
import { ArrowRight } from 'lucide-astro';

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "How Paid Link Prices Rose While Their Value Collapsed",
  "description": "Primary-source pricing analysis of editorial coverage and link marketplace rates from 140,000+ publisher listings and six years of agency snapshots.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Daniel Grainger",
    "url": "https://ranking-atlas.com/about",
    "jobTitle": "Founder",
    "worksFor": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Ranking Atlas",
      "url": "https://ranking-atlas.com"
    },
    "sameAs": [
      "https://www.linkedin.com/in/daniel-grainger/",
      "https://ranking-atlas.com/about"
    ]
  },
  "datePublished": "2026-03-01",
  "dateModified": "2026-04-01",
  "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Ranking Atlas" }
};
---

<Layout
  title="How Paid Link Prices Rose While Their Value Collapsed — Ranking Atlas"
  description="Primary-source pricing analysis of editorial coverage and link marketplace rates from 140,000+ publisher listings, 2020–2026."
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(jsonLd)} />

<article class="py-20 md:py-28">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-brand font-medium mb-3">Data Report</div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink leading-[1.1] mb-6">
      How Paid Link Prices Rose While Their Value Collapsed
    </h1>
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
      <a href="/about" class="shrink-0">
        <img src="/assets/images/author/daniel-headshot.jpg" alt="Daniel Grainger" class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full object-cover" width="48" height="48" />
      </a>
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-ink">By <a href="/about" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark transition-colors">Daniel Grainger</a>, founder of Ranking Atlas</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#64748B]">Published March 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Based on 140,000+ publisher listings</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative w-full rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-surface border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 shadow-card mb-10 aspect-[16/9] flex items-center justify-center">
      <img
        src="/assets/images/resources/the-cost-of-authority/hero.jpg"
        alt="How Paid Link Prices Rose While Their Value Collapsed"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
        onerror="this.style.display='none';this.nextElementSibling.style.display='flex'"
      />
      <div class="hidden flex-col items-center justify-center text-muted p-8 text-center">
        <div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-brand font-medium mb-3">Hero Image Slot</div>
        <div class="text-sm">Drop hero.jpg into /public/assets/images/resources/the-cost-of-authority/ when ready.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-body text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-4">
      Paid links are more expensive than they've ever been. They're also less effective than they've ever been.
    </p>
    <p class="text-body text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-4">
      Demand for backlinks has climbed as more brands compete for coverage, but at the same time, Google has been deindexing low-authority sites in waves since the <a href="https://developers.google.com/search/blog/2022/08/helpful-content-update" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark underline underline-offset-2">Helpful Content Update rolled out in 2022</a>. Those are the sites most paid links live on. A link on a deindexed site passes no authority, drives no referral traffic, and can't be cited by anything, human or machine.
    </p>
    <p class="text-body text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-6">
      This report uses six years of pricing data across 140,000+ paid link listings from major marketplaces to analyze the price of links over time, and how much of what's being sold still matters.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-white border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 rounded-xl p-6 mb-10 shadow-card">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink mb-3">In this report, you'll see:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-[#475569] mb-4 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>What marketplace links actually cost in 2026, by Domain Rating and real organic traffic</li>
        <li>Why Domain Rating alone misprices the signal, and what correlates with real value</li>
        <li>How agency-managed and publisher-direct prices have diverged, 2020–2026</li>
        <li>How indexing is destroying paid link value overnight</li>
        <li>What the economics look like for paid vs. earned coverage, annualised across useful lifespan</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#64748B] italic">Let's start with what the market charges today.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 text-left">
        <div class="group bg-white rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 p-6 shadow-card transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-[0_8px_30px_-8px_rgba(93,79,224,0.2)] hover:border-[#5D4FE0]/20 relative">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#94A3B8] mb-2">Avg. guest post cost</p>
          <p class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black tracking-tight text-ink mb-1">$365</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[#64748B]">Direct from publisher</p>
          <div class="hidden group-hover:block absolute bottom-full left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 mb-2 w-64 bg-[#0A0F1E] text-white text-xs rounded-lg p-3 leading-relaxed z-10 pointer-events-none">
            The average price a publisher charges for a single guest post placement, bought directly through a marketplace. This is the base cost before any vendor or agency markup.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="group bg-white rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 p-6 shadow-card transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-[0_8px_30px_-8px_rgba(93,79,224,0.2)] hover:border-[#5D4FE0]/20 relative">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#94A3B8] mb-2">Avg. vendor markup</p>
          <p class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black tracking-tight text-ink mb-1">75%</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[#64748B]">Buying through intermediaries</p>
          <div class="hidden group-hover:block absolute bottom-full left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 mb-2 w-64 bg-[#0A0F1E] text-white text-xs rounded-lg p-3 leading-relaxed z-10 pointer-events-none">
            When you buy through an agency or managed service instead of directly on a marketplace, you pay an average of 75% more. A $365 direct placement becomes ~$638 through an intermediary.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="group bg-white rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 p-6 shadow-card transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-[0_8px_30px_-8px_rgba(93,79,224,0.2)] hover:border-[#5D4FE0]/20 relative">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#94A3B8] mb-2">Quality-filtered avg.</p>
          <p class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black tracking-tight text-ink mb-1">$930</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[#64748B]">DR50+ with real traffic</p>
          <div class="hidden group-hover:block absolute bottom-full left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 mb-2 w-64 bg-[#0A0F1E] text-white text-xs rounded-lg p-3 leading-relaxed z-10 pointer-events-none">
            When you filter marketplace listings to only include sites with DR50+ and real organic traffic (1,000+ monthly visitors), the average price jumps to $930. Quality links cost far more than the headline average suggests.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="group bg-white rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 p-6 shadow-card transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-[0_8px_30px_-8px_rgba(93,79,224,0.2)] hover:border-[#5D4FE0]/20 relative">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#94A3B8] mb-2">Meet quality bar</p>
          <p class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black tracking-tight text-ink mb-1">4.6%</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[#64748B]">Of all marketplace listings</p>
          <div class="hidden group-hover:block absolute bottom-full left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 mb-2 w-64 bg-[#0A0F1E] text-white text-xs rounded-lg p-3 leading-relaxed z-10 pointer-events-none">
            Of all guest post sites on marketplaces, only 4.6% meet basic quality criteria: minimum DR40 and minimum 1,000 monthly organic traffic. The other 95.4% are unlikely to deliver meaningful authority signal.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#94A3B8] mt-4 text-center">Stat sources: <a href="https://www.buzzstream.com/blog/guest-post-sites/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark underline underline-offset-2">BuzzStream guest post analysis (2025)</a>, <a href="https://adsy.com/blog/backlink-pricing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark underline underline-offset-2">Adsy pricing study (2025)</a>. Full methodology below.</p>
    </div>
</article>

  <!-- ── SECTION 1: What The 2026 Marketplace Actually Charges ── -->
  <section id="data" class="py-16 md:py-24" style="background: #F8F7FA;">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-5">
        1. What The 2026 Marketplace Actually Charges
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-[#475569] leading-relaxed mb-8 font-medium max-w-3xl">
        These are the direct marketplace prices agencies and brands pay for a single placement. Buy through an intermediary and you'll pay 75% more on top.
      </p>

      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 shadow-card mb-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-[#F1F5F9]">
              <th class="text-left px-6 py-4 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#64748B]">DR Range</th>
              <th class="text-left px-6 py-4 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#64748B]">Guest Post</th>
              <th class="text-left px-6 py-4 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#64748B]">Niche Edit</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-[#0A0F1E]/6">
            <tr class="bg-white hover:bg-[#F8F7FA] transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-[#0A0F1E]">DR 10–20</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$70–150</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$49–100</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-[#F8F7FA]/50 hover:bg-[#F8F7FA] transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-[#0A0F1E]">DR 20–30</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$100–250</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$75–225</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white hover:bg-[#F8F7FA] transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-[#0A0F1E]">DR 30–40</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$150–400</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$150–350</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-[#F8F7FA]/50 hover:bg-[#F8F7FA] transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-[#0A0F1E]">DR 40–50</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$250–600</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$250–400</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white hover:bg-[#F8F7FA] transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-[#0A0F1E]">DR 50–60</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$400–700</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$350–600</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-[#F8F7FA]/50 hover:bg-[#F8F7FA] transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-[#0A0F1E]">DR 60–70</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$500–1,000</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$500–700</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white hover:bg-[#F8F7FA] transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-[#0A0F1E]">DR 70–80</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$800–2,000</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$700–1,000+</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-[#F8F7FA]/50 hover:bg-[#F8F7FA] transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-[#0A0F1E]">DR 80+</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$1,500–10,000+</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$1,000+</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-[#94A3B8] mb-8">Prices reflect direct marketplace rates. Buying through a vendor or managed service typically adds a 75% markup.</p>

      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-base text-[#475569] leading-relaxed font-semibold mb-4">The range is the story.</p>
        <p class="text-base text-[#475569] leading-relaxed mb-4">A DR80+ placement costs 10–100x more than a DR20. The top tier is where the publisher-direct premium lives. The headline averages hide enormous variance within each tier.</p>
        <p class="text-base text-[#475569] leading-relaxed mb-6">A $365 average conceals the reality: if you need a placement that actually moves AI and search signals, you are buying in the DR50+ range at $400–700 per placement, minimum.</p>

        <div class="border-l-4 border-brand bg-white rounded-r-xl pl-5 pr-4 py-4 shadow-card">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink mb-1">Note:</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[#475569] leading-relaxed">Every price in this table is for a paid placement. The publisher is paid to run your content. By Google's definition, that is a link scheme. Risk and value both change accordingly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── SECTION 2: Why Domain Rating Alone Misprices The Signal ── -->
  <section id="heatmap" class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-5 max-w-3xl">
        2. Why Domain Rating Alone Misprices The Signal
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-[#475569] leading-relaxed mb-8 font-medium max-w-3xl">
        DR measures a site's backlink profile. It does not measure whether anyone actually reads the site. Marketplaces price on DR anyway.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 shadow-card p-6 mb-8 overflow-x-auto">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#94A3B8] mb-4">Average guest post price (USD) by DR and monthly organic traffic</p>
        <div id="heatmapEl"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-base text-[#475569] leading-relaxed mb-4">Two numbers explain the mispricing.</p>
        <p class="text-base text-[#475569] leading-relaxed mb-4">19% of marketplace guest post sites receive fewer than 100 monthly organic visitors. Many of them still charge mid-tier prices. A $300 link on a zero-traffic DR50 site delivers less ranking value than a $150 link on a DR30 site with 10,000 real visitors.</p>
        <p class="text-base text-[#475569] leading-relaxed mb-6">At the high end, 53% of DR71+ sites fall into mid- or low-quality tiers because they have under 50,000 monthly organic traffic. High DR without traffic is a red flag.</p>

        <p class="text-base text-[#475569] leading-relaxed font-semibold mb-4">Here's what that means in practice:</p>
        <p class="text-base text-[#475569] leading-relaxed mb-6">Any buyer using DR as their primary filter is overpaying for signal. Traffic is the cleaner proxy. Editorial quality is cleaner still. Neither is priced accurately by the marketplace.</p>

        <div class="border-l-4 border-brand bg-white rounded-r-xl pl-5 pr-4 py-4 shadow-card">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink mb-1">Pro tip:</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[#475569] leading-relaxed">When auditing a marketplace listing, divide the price by monthly organic traffic. A DR50 site charging $300 with 500 visitors costs $0.60 per monthly visitor reached. A DR30 site charging $150 with 10,000 visitors costs $0.015 per visitor. The DR30 site is 40x more efficient on that measure.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── SECTION 3: How Agency And Publisher-Direct Prices Have Diverged ── -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24" style="background: #F8F7FA;">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-5 max-w-3xl">
        3. How Agency And Publisher-Direct Prices Have Diverged
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-[#475569] leading-relaxed mb-8 max-w-3xl">
        Primary-source Wayback data for five established link agencies, 2020 to 2026. Each data point is a verified snapshot of what the agency charged in that year. DR30+ equivalent tier shown, the most commonly listed tier across all vendors and years.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-card p-6 md:p-10 mb-4">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 780 440" class="w-full h-auto" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-labelledby="chart-title chart-desc">
          <title id="chart-title">Agency DR30+ link prices, 2020 to 2026</title>
          <desc id="chart-desc">Line chart showing per-link pricing over time for FATJOE, Searcharoo, Loganix, RhinoRank, and a publisher-direct industry benchmark.</desc>
          <g stroke="#E5E7EB" stroke-width="1">
            <line x1="80" y1="60"  x2="740" y2="60"/>
            <line x1="80" y1="124" x2="740" y2="124"/>
            <line x1="80" y1="188" x2="740" y2="188"/>
            <line x1="80" y1="252" x2="740" y2="252"/>
            <line x1="80" y1="316" x2="740" y2="316"/>
            <line x1="80" y1="380" x2="740" y2="380" stroke="#9CA3AF"/>
          </g>
          <g font-family="ui-sans-serif, system-ui" font-size="12" fill="#6B7280" text-anchor="end">
            <text x="70" y="64">$250</text>
            <text x="70" y="128">$200</text>
            <text x="70" y="192">$150</text>
            <text x="70" y="256">$100</text>
            <text x="70" y="320">$50</text>
            <text x="70" y="384">$0</text>
          </g>
          <g font-family="ui-sans-serif, system-ui" font-size="12" fill="#6B7280" text-anchor="middle">
            <text x="110" y="405">2020</text>
            <text x="215" y="405">2021</text>
            <text x="320" y="405">2022</text>
            <text x="425" y="405">2023</text>
            <text x="530" y="405">2024</text>
            <text x="635" y="405">2025</text>
            <text x="740" y="405">2026</text>
          </g>
          <g stroke="#5D4FE0" stroke-width="2.5" fill="none">
            <polyline points="110,259 215,276 635,227 740,227"/>
          </g>
          <g fill="#5D4FE0">
            <circle cx="110" cy="259" r="4"/>
            <circle cx="215" cy="276" r="4"/>
            <circle cx="635" cy="227" r="4"/>
            <circle cx="740" cy="227" r="4"/>
          </g>
          <g stroke="#059669" stroke-width="2.5" fill="none" stroke-dasharray="6 3">
            <polyline points="110,209 530,124 635,124 740,124"/>
          </g>
          <g fill="#059669">
            <circle cx="110" cy="209" r="4"/>
            <circle cx="530" cy="124" r="4"/>
            <circle cx="635" cy="124" r="4"/>
            <circle cx="740" cy="124" r="4"/>
          </g>
          <g stroke="#DB2777" stroke-width="2.5" fill="none">
            <polyline points="320,230 635,150"/>
          </g>
          <g fill="#DB2777">
            <circle cx="320" cy="230" r="4"/>
            <circle cx="635" cy="150" r="4"/>
          </g>
          <g stroke="#D97706" stroke-width="2.5" fill="none">
            <polyline points="320,227 740,227"/>
          </g>
          <g fill="#D97706">
            <circle cx="320" cy="227" r="4"/>
            <circle cx="740" cy="227" r="4"/>
          </g>
          <g stroke="#6B7280" stroke-width="2" fill="none" stroke-dasharray="2 3">
            <polyline points="110,342 530,264"/>
          </g>
          <g fill="#6B7280">
            <circle cx="110" cy="342" r="3"/>
            <circle cx="530" cy="264" r="3"/>
          </g>
          <g font-family="ui-sans-serif, system-ui" font-size="13" fill="#374151">
            <g transform="translate(100, 30)">
              <rect width="14" height="3" y="5" fill="#5D4FE0"/>
              <text x="22" y="10">FATJOE</text>
            </g>
            <g transform="translate(200, 30)">
              <line x1="0" y1="6" x2="14" y2="6" stroke="#059669" stroke-width="3" stroke-dasharray="4 2"/>
              <text x="22" y="10">Loganix</text>
            </g>
            <g transform="translate(300, 30)">
              <rect width="14" height="3" y="5" fill="#DB2777"/>
              <text x="22" y="10">Searcharoo</text>
            </g>
            <g transform="translate(420, 30)">
              <rect width="14" height="3" y="5" fill="#D97706"/>
              <text x="22" y="10">RhinoRank</text>
            </g>
            <g transform="translate(540, 30)">
              <line x1="0" y1="6" x2="14" y2="6" stroke="#6B7280" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="2 2"/>
              <text x="22" y="10">Publisher-direct (FatRank)</text>
            </g>
          </g>
        </svg>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-muted italic mb-8">Lines connect only the years for which a given vendor has a verified snapshot. Gaps reflect missing Wayback coverage for that URL in that year, not pricing gaps.</p>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink leading-snug mb-3">Per-Vendor Pricing, DR30+ Equivalent</h3>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl shadow-card bg-white">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead class="bg-bg-paper text-ink">
              <tr>
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Vendor</th>
                <th class="text-right px-4 py-3 font-semibold">2020</th>
                <th class="text-right px-4 py-3 font-semibold">2021</th>
